@node Mountlist "Mountlist for ZIP"
@prev History

On Amiga computer mountlist is useful  for  ZIP  drive  since  Amiga  does  not
not recognize ZIP drive when no disk was present at boottime.

@endnode

@node Password "Password"
@prev Mountlist

@{b}Password@{ub}

Don't know the password on the write-protected  original  ziptools
disk you received together with your ZIP drive? Well you don't have to
know it. Starting with version 2.0 of  @{b}ZipTools@{ub}  you  can  cancel  the
password  by  simply  erasing  whole  disk  but you will also lose all
ziptools  program  saved  there (this disk  contains programs only for
Macintosh  or  PC  computers).  If  you  want  to keep them simply try
unprotect disk with the following password :

                          @{b}APlaceForYourStuff@{ub}

                          @{b}APlaceForMyStuff@{ub}

But there is no guarantee it will  work  on  all  ziptool  disks  from
IOMEGA.


@endnode

@node Write_button "Write button"

Clicking this button will write-protect disk in drive.

@endnode

@node Read_button "Read button"

Clicking this button will read-protect disk in drive with password.

@endnode

@node Writepsw_button "Write with password button"

Clicking this button will write-protect disk in drive with password.

@endnode

@node GR_grp_3C "Write-protection group"

Three buttons in this group will set write-protection on disk.

@endnode

@node Eject "Eject button"

This button will eject disk currently in drive.

@endnode

@node Motor "Motor button"

This button will stop motor.

@endnode

@node Forever "Forever button"

This button will unprotect disk currently in drive. Password  will  be
erased.

@endnode

@node Until_eject "Until eject button"

This button will unprotect disk currently in drive. Password  will  be
restored after disk removal.

@endnode

@node Unprotect_group "Unprotect group"

Two buttons control disk-protection removal.

@endnode

@node Disk_group "Disk group"

Two buttons in this group will stop motor or eject disk.

@endnode

@node Protect_disk "Protection group"

Buttons in this group will set protection on disk in drive.

@endnode

@node Erase "Erase disk button"

This buttons will clear all disk.
This enables also to clear forgotten password.
But beware! ALL DATA ON DISK WILL BE LOST!

@endnode

@node Get_Sleep "Get sleep button"

ZIP drives feature a automatic shutdown of  motor  after  a  specified
time. You may get this time by clicking this button.

@endnode

@node Set_Sleep "Set sleep button"

ZIP drives feature a automatic shutdown of  motor  after  a  specified
time.  You  may  set  this time by clicking this button. Entering 0 in
requester window will disable this feature.

@endnode

@node Sleep_group "Sleep group"

ZIP drives feature a automatic shutdown of  motor  after  a  specified
time.  You  may  set  or  get  this  time  by clicking one of this two
buttons.

@endnode

@node Str_2_password "Password string gadget"

Enter password into this gadget. Maximum 255 characters.

@endnode

@node Str_2_repeat "Repeat password string gadget"

Confirm password by entering it again into this gadget.

@endnode

@node Str_3_device "Scsi device name"

Every scsi hardware controller is communicates with scsi devices  with
software  scsi  device.  You  must enter name of scsi device into this
gadget. If you own Blizzard SCSI controller name  is  1230scsi.device.
See hardware manual for name of scsi device.

@endnode

@node Str_3_id "Scsi id number"

Every scsi hardware has its own unique ID number.
You may have up to 7 hardware devices connected to your
scsi controller. ZIP drives are using only ID 5 or 6.
See back of your drive to find out correct ID.

@endnode

@node Busy_group "Busy window"

Busy window opens up when program is doing some time consuming task
like clearing all disk.

@endnode

@node Status "Status line"

This text shows status of ZIP drive.

@endnode
